### Frontend Component

#### [MODIFY] [api.js](file:///c:/Users/admin/HBD_Chatbot/src/services/api.js)
*   Create a reusable helper wrapper `makeRequest(url, options)` that:
    *   Fetches the saved token from `localStorage`.
    *   Injects the `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header dynamically if the token exists.
    *   Wraps all fetch requests with this helper.
    *   Checks if the response returns a `401 Unauthorized` status. If so, removes the token from `localStorage` and triggers a reload/logout to reset frontend state cleanly.
*   Hook into response chains for `login` and `verifyEmailOtp` to capture and commit `res.token` to `localStorage`.

#### [MODIFY] [App.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/HBD_Chatbot/src/App.jsx)
*   Add a React `useEffect` hook listening to the global `isLoggedIn` state.
*   Remove the `token` key from `localStorage` whenever `isLoggedIn` transitions to `false` (handling logout gracefully across all components).

